- Previously, we completed the declaration and initialization of arrays. Now, we will learn how to iterate through a two-dimensional (2D) array using nested loops in C.

- A 2D array stores data in rows and columns. To access every element, we use nested loops: the outer loop goes through each row, and the inner loop goes through each column within that row.

